(footprint "SW_Dailywell_DW5_DPDT" (version 20221018) (generator pcbnew)
  (layer "F.Cu")
  (descr "Dailywell DW5 (2M series) sub-miniature toggle switch, DPDT ON-ON-ON, PCB through-hole (M2 PC thru-hole terminals). 6 pins in a 2x3 grid: pin pitch 2.54 mm within each row, 5.08 mm row-to-row. Row 1 = pins 1,2,3 (pole A, pin 2 = common); row 2 = pins 4,5,6 (pole B, pin 5 = common). Body 8.13 x 9.14 mm; courtyard 8.63 x 9.64 mm; panel hole Ø4.95 mm. Origin = bushing/actuator centre (panel anchor). Datasheet: Dailywell 2M series (nitron-components / Tayda). DW5 shares the same DPDT body and land pattern as DW3; only the internal contact behaviour differs (ON-ON-ON vs ON-ON).")
